fix: remove multihash digest from the prefix
body:
Removing the cd multihash digest from the message.  It's not needed and not expected by some implementations.
https://github.com/ipfs/helia/blob/c0bf36eb45ae0551a1c406e5b806d01425abb1f9/packages/bitswap/src/want-list.ts#L371

title: fix: remove unused dependencies
body:
* `void` is unused
* ~The `time` note seems to no longer apply~

title: fix: Print payload size instead of content to avoid large `Debug` size for `Event`
body:
This is more of a suggestion, if you don't think it's a good improvement we're all good. 

However, while debugging events in the polka-storage project, I got absolutely spammed by the data field (our payload has a length of ~262k).

I picked 32 more or less at random, but of course, I'm open to suggestions.

title: chore: Add note about hashers in readme
body:
First off, thanks for making a bitswap in Rust! This is great.

Once I started using it, I did lose my mind as to why some bit were not swapping.

After digging, finding the `hashers` module, I realized hashers need to be explicitly added.

Since it's not evidently clear on the front page that the hashers need to be explicitly "added", this readme note is an attempt to correct that.

Hopefully this will save someone else some time!

feat: Add helpers for MultihasherError
body:
With this helper a user can replace

```rust
.map_err(|e| MultihasherError::CustomFatal(e.to_string()))
```

with

```rust
.map_err(MultihasherError::custom_fatal)
```
